        <body>
            <entry xml:id="entry_ædyly" xml:lang="os">
                <form xml:id="form_d4744e66" xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>ædyly</orth></form>
                <form xml:id="form_d4744e69" xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>æduli</orth></form>
                <sense xml:id="sense_d4744e72"><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                        <q>глупый</q>
                    </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                        <q>stupid</q>
                    </abv:tr></sense>
                <abv:exampleGrp xml:id="exampleGrp_d4744e82">
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d4744e84">
                        <quote>wydis dywwæ ʽvsymæry; īw ʒy wydī zændǵyn, īnnæ ædyly</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>было два брата; один из них был умный, другой глупый</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>there were two brothers; one of them was smart, the other was
                                stupid</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Munk."/><biblScope>146</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d4744e103">
                        <quote>ædylyjy fændaggag razdær fæxærync</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>дорожная провизия глупого съедается в начале (пути)</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>travel provisions of the stupid are eaten at the beginning (of the
                                road)</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ЮОПам."/><biblScope>III
                            234</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d4744e122" xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>wæd ma mæ xonæntæ æduli!</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>пусть тогда еще назовут меня дурнем!</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>then let them still call me a fool!</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Gurdž._Æduli"/><biblScope>77</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d4744e144" xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>næ færazun mæ mednimær kænun mæxe ædulijæn ænkʼaj</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>не могу представить, чтобы я стала супругой дурака</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>I can not imagine that I would become the wife of a fool</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Gurdž._Æduli"/><biblScope>89</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">Ср. <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d4744e257" xml:id="mentioned_d4744e169" xml:lang="trk"><lang/>
                        <w>deli, däli</w>
                        <gloss><q>глупый</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d4744e265" xml:id="mentioned_d4744e177" xml:lang="trk"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>дурак</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d4744e271" xml:id="mentioned_d4744e183" xml:lang="trk"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>сумасшедший</q></gloss></mentioned>; проникло и в другие
                    кавказские языки: <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d4744e277" xml:id="mentioned_d4744e189" xml:lang="kbd"><lang/>
                        <w>delä, dejlä</w>
                        <gloss><q>глупый</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d4744e285" xml:id="mentioned_d4744e197" xml:lang="kbd"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>дурак</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d4744e292" xml:id="mentioned_d4744e204" xml:lang="lez"><lang/>
                        <w>deli</w>
                        <gloss><q>сумасшедший</q></gloss></mentioned>. Появление в начале <hi rendition="#rend_italic">æ</hi>,
                    осмысляемого, по-видимому, как α privativum, явилось результатом восприятия
                    этого слова как негативного: „не-разумный“, „без-умный“. Может быть, сыграла
                    также роль контаминация с <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d4744e300" xml:id="mentioned_d4744e212" xml:lang="ar"><lang/>
                        <w>abdāl</w>
                        <gloss><q>отшельник</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d4744e308" xml:id="mentioned_d4744e220" xml:lang="ar"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>безумец</q></gloss></mentioned>, ср. <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d4744e314" xml:id="mentioned_d4744e226" xml:lang="av"><lang/>
                        <w>’adal-</w>
                        <gloss><q>глупый</q></gloss></mentioned>. <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Miller._Gr."/><biblScope>80</biblScope></bibl> выводил
                    из <hi rendition="#rend_italic">*a-turya</hi>, ср. <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d4744e326" xml:id="mentioned_d4744e238" xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>turas</w>
                        <gloss><q>мощный</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d4744e335" xml:id="mentioned_d4744e247" xml:lang="sa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>быстрый</q></gloss></mentioned>. Однако значения плохо
                    вяжутся.</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">Cf. <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d4744e169" xml:id="mentioned_d4744e257" xml:lang="trk"><lang/>
                        <w>deli, däli</w>
                        <gloss><q>stupid</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d4744e177" xml:id="mentioned_d4744e265" xml:lang="trk"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>fool</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d4744e183" xml:id="mentioned_d4744e271" xml:lang="trk"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>crazy</q></gloss></mentioned>; found its way into other Caucasian
                    languages: <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d4744e189" xml:id="mentioned_d4744e277" xml:lang="kbd"><lang/>
                        <w>delä, dejlä</w>
                        <gloss><q>stupid</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d4744e197" xml:id="mentioned_d4744e285" xml:lang="kbd"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>fool</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d4744e204" xml:id="mentioned_d4744e292" xml:lang="lez"><lang/>
                        <w>deli</w>
                        <gloss><q>crazy</q></gloss></mentioned>. The appearance of <hi rendition="#rend_italic">æ</hi> at the
                    beginning, which was treated, apparently, as α privativum, was the result of the
                    fact that this word was percepted as negative: “not-intelligent”,
                    “without-intelligent”. Perhaps, contamination with <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d4744e212" xml:id="mentioned_d4744e300" xml:lang="ar"><lang/>
                        <w>abdāl</w>
                        <gloss><q>hermit</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d4744e220" xml:id="mentioned_d4744e308" xml:lang="ar"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>madman</q></gloss></mentioned> played its role, cf. <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d4744e226" xml:id="mentioned_d4744e314" xml:lang="av"><lang/>
                        <w>’adal-</w>
                        <gloss><q>stupid</q></gloss></mentioned>. <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Miller._Gr."/><biblScope>80</biblScope></bibl> traced
                    it back to <hi rendition="#rend_italic">*a-turya</hi>, cf. <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d4744e238" xml:id="mentioned_d4744e326" xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>turas</w>
                        <gloss><q>powerful</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d4744e247" xml:id="mentioned_d4744e335" xml:lang="sa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>fast</q></gloss></mentioned>. However, the meanings do not fit
                    well.</etym>
            </entry>
